

<h2>Description of Materials</h2>


<p>The court records for the sessions of the Circuit Court of the District of Columbia held at Washington are located at the National Archives in Washington, D.C., as "Records of the U.S. District Court for the District of Columbia," Record Group 21.6, "Case Papers, 1802-63," National Archives and Records Administration, Washington, D.C. Those cases heard before the Court at Alexandria sessions are held elsewhere, at the Library of Virginia in Richmond.</p>

